SEARCH
Package com.bobocode.bring.core.context

Interface BringBeanFactory

All Known Implementing Classes:
AnnotationBringBeanRegistry, BringApplicationContext, DefaultBringBeanFactory
public interface BringBeanFactory
An interface representing a simplified Bean Factory, allowing retrieval of beans by type or name. Implementations of this interface provide methods to retrieve beans based on specified criteria.
Since:
1.0
Author:
Blyzhnytsia Team

    • getBeans

      <T> Map<String,T> getBeans(Class<T> type)
      Retrieve a map of beans of the specified type, where the key is the bean name and the value is the bean instance.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of the beans.
      Parameters:
      type - The class/type of the beans to retrieve.
      Returns:
      A map containing bean names as keys and corresponding bean instances as values or throw NoSuchBeanException

    • getAllBeans

      <T> Map<String,T> getAllBeans()

      T - The type of the beans.
      Returns:
      A map containing all registered bean names as keys and corresponding bean instances as values.
